channel.title: Error when trying to open an interface
channel.description:
When i try to open an interface like this:
[code] } else if (playerCommand.startsWith("resetstat")) { c.showInterface(2808);[/code]
I get an error in my compiler like this: [IMG]http://i41.tinypic.com/34qnv3o.png[/img]
I know it means i dont have the public void or whatever but how do i find out which one i have so i can open the interface with that command?

item.description:
@Skiire wrote:

Use a program that has method searching when you’re programming. (Eclipse)

Simply put the showInterface method isn’t in the client class. It’s in the PlayerAssistant class.

c.getPA().showInterface(2808);
